Fitch said South Africa's outlook revision reflects a marked widening in the budget deficit as a result of lower GDP growth and increased spending. JOHANNESBURG - Ratings agency Fitch on Friday revised its outlook for South Africa to negative but has affirmed its rating at BB+. It said it had revised its outlook on South Africa's long-term foreign-currency rating to negative from stable. Fitch said South Africa's outlook revision reflected a marked widening in the budget deficit as a result of a lower GDP growth and increased spending. Moody's was the only agency of the big three that has South Africa in positive territory.